        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued June 2 at 7:36PM PDT until June 2 at 9:45PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>At 736 PM PDT, Doppler radar continued to indicate thunderstorms
producing heavy rain near Coyote Springs and along the US-93
corridor north of Apex. Flash flooding is ongoing or expected to
begin shortly. A rain gage at Elbow Mountain reported 1.54 inches of
rain in less than one hour.

HAZARD...Life-threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...Radar.

IMPACT...Life-threatening flash flooding of low-water crossings,
creeks, normally dry washes and roads.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Sr 168 Mile Marker 21 and Coyote Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
